Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
createSpecialMarkLayerShape(25.10)          createSpecialMarkLayerShape(25.10)

Name
       createSpecialMarkLayerShape - Creates a mark layer shape, using special
       route

Syntax
       createSpecialMarkLayerShape

       [-help]

       [-cutOutBlockInsts <string>]

       [-extendOuterX <float>]

       [-extendOuterY <float>]

       [-extendX <float>]

       [-extendY <float>]

       -layer <string>

       Creates  a  mark layer shape, using special route. This command enables
       you to apply one set of rules for the entire design in Innovus by  con-
       necting  the  macro pins around halo of IP blocks. The IPs are selected
       based on a list which provides the instance name.

Parameters
       -cutOutBlockInsts <string>
              Specifies the name of the instances that are to be cut out.

              Note: All blocks are cut out if -cutOutBlockInsts is not  speci-
              fied  however,  if  -cutOutBlockInsts  {}  is specified then all
              blocks are NOT cut as this pattern cannot match anything.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -extendOuterX <float>
              Expands the mark layer shape in X direction.

              Data_type: float, optional

       -extendOuterY <float>
              Expands the mark layer shape in Y direction.

              Data_type: float, optional

       -extendX <float>
              Expands the no-mark layer shape in X direction.

              Data_type: float, optional

       -extendY <float>
              Expands the no-mark layer shape in Y direction.

              Data_type: float, optional

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each createSpecialMarkLayerShape parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man createSpecialMarkLayerShape

       -layer <string>
              Specifies  the names of the layers on which the mark layer shape
              is to be applied.

              Data_type: string, required

Example
              * The following command creates a mark  layer  shape  on  M2_P48
                that  blocks  out DTMF_INST/PLLCLK_INST and expands the marker
                layer shape by 10 in X direction and by 20 in Y direction:

                createSpecialMarkLayerShape  -cutOutBlockInsts  DTMF_INST/PLL-
                CLK_INST -extendOuterX 10 -extendOuterY 20 -layer M2_P48

              * The  following  command  creates  a mark layer shape on M2_P48
                that blocks out DTMF_INST/PLLCLK_INST and expands the  no-mark
                layer shape by 10 in X direction and by 20 in Y direction:

                createSpecialMarkLayerShape  -cutOutBlockInsts  DTMF_INST/PLL-
                CLK_INST -extendX 10 -extendY 20 -layer M2_P48

